>
  <main id="main"><header class="page-hero page-hero--portrait"><div class="container"><div class="breadcrumbs"><a href="index.html">Home</a> / <a href="missions.html">Missions</a> / Science</div><span class="kicker">Humanity-scale mission</span><h1>Science & Discovery</h1><p>Advancing research, scientific inquiry, frontier discovery, science communication, public-interest technology, and evidence-based service.</p></div></header><nav class="anchor-nav anchor-nav--bar" aria-label="On this page"><div class="container"><a href="#focus"><span>01</span>Areas of focus</a><a href="#overview"><span>02</span>Overview</a><a href="#principles"><span>03</span>Principles</a><a href="#process"><span>04</span>How it works</a><a href="#next"><span>05</span>Next steps</a></div></nav><section class="section focus-gallery" id="focus"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro section-intro--center"><span class="eyebrow">The field of action</span><h2>Where this mission concentrates disciplined effort</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Science Fellows advance knowledge while respecting the methods, uncertainty, ethics, and collaborative institutions on which credible discovery depends.</p></div><div class="focus-gallery__grid"><article class="dimension-card"><span>01</span><LegacyIcon name="compass" /><h3>Research and discovery</h3><p>Support well-framed questions, rigorous methods, analysis, replication, and new knowledge.</p></article><article class="dimension-card"><span>02</span><LegacyIcon name="institution" /><h3>Scientific capacity</h3><p>Strengthen data, laboratories, research operations, open tools, workforce, and institutional systems.</p></article><article class="dimension-card"><span>03</span><LegacyIcon name="lightbulb-o" /><h3>Translation and communication</h3><p>Make evidence understandable and useful without overstating certainty or erasing important limits.</p></article><article class="dimension-card"><span>04</span><LegacyIcon name="handshake-o" /><h3>Science in public life</h3><p>Help institutions and communities use evidence responsibly in decisions of public consequence.</p></article></div></div></section><section class="split-opening" id="overview"><div class="split-opening__copy"><div class="prose"><span class="eyebrow">A humanity-scale mission</span><h2>Inquiry in service to understanding and public benefit</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Science Fellows advance knowledge while respecting the methods, uncertainty, ethics, and collaborative institutions on which credible discovery depends.</p><p>Contributions may occur at the frontier of research or in the essential work of synthesis, infrastructure, communication, translation, and public understanding.</p><p>Research and discovery establishes the point of entry; science in public life defines what should remain after the immediate work is complete.</p></div></div><div class="split-opening__visual"><span>01</span><p>Research and discovery establishes the point of entry; science in public life defines what should remain after the immediate work is complete.</p></div></section><section class="section" id="principles"><div class="container principle-sidebar"><aside><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">Mission guardrails</span><h2>How ambitious work remains responsible</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Scale increases the need for context, collaboration, and durable public value.</p></div></aside><div class="grid grid--3"><article class="card card--numbered"><span class="card__number">01</span><h3>Listen before acting</h3><p>Understand existing knowledge, lived experience, and institutional context before defining a response. In this context, consider research and discovery.</p></article><article class="card card--numbered"><span class="card__number">02</span><h3>Work across boundaries</h3><p>Bring disciplines and sectors together when no single profession can address the whole challenge. In this context, consider scientific capacity.</p></article><article class="card card--numbered"><span class="card__number">03</span><h3>Build durable capacity</h3><p>Favor work that strengthens people, knowledge, and systems beyond the immediate intervention. In this context, consider translation and communication.</p></article></div></div></section><section class="section" id="process"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">From intent to practice</span><h2>From a large mission to useful work</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Humanity-scale language must lead to specific contribution. Each appointment narrows a broad challenge into work a Fellow and host can pursue responsibly.</p></div><div class="steps"><article class="step"><h3>Understand the field</h3><p>Map the challenge, affected communities, existing efforts, evidence, and important constraints. Here, attend to research and discovery: Support well-framed questions, rigorous methods, analysis, replication, and new knowledge.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>Locate leverage</h3><p>Identify a bounded question or institutional need where the Fellow&#x27;s capabilities can matter. Here, attend to scientific capacity: Strengthen data, laboratories, research operations, open tools, workforce, and institutional systems.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>Contribute with discipline</h3><p>Work through a trusted host, respect domain knowledge, and produce useful, reviewable outputs. Here, attend to translation and communication: Make evidence understandable and useful without overstating certainty or erasing important limits.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>Strengthen what endures</h3><p>Share learning and reinforce the relationships, knowledge, and systems that carry the mission forward. Here, attend to science in public life: Help institutions and communities use evidence responsibly in decisions of public consequence.</p></article></div></div></section><section class="section close-seal" id="next"><div class="container"><span class="close-seal__mark" aria-hidden="true">USF</span><div><h2>Translate a large mission into useful work</h2><p>Begin with research and discovery, then define a contribution your capabilities or institution can support.</p></div><div class="actions"><a class="button button--gold" href="apply.html">Express interest</a><a class="button button--outline" href="missions.html">Explore all missions</a></div><aside class="related-panel"><span class="eyebrow">Continue exploring</span><h3>Related pathways</h3><ul class="related-list"><li><a href="missions.html">All missions</a></li><li><a href="mission-fellowships.html">Mission Fellowships</a></li><li><a href="fellowship-programs.html">Fellowship programs</a></li></ul></aside></div></section></main>

